7. Comments explaining each change

## IMPLEMENTATION REQUIREMENTS

### Code Quality
- Follow existing code style in the repository
- Include docstrings/comments for new functions
- Use async/await patterns for I/O operations
- Proper error handling with try-catch and logging
- Type hints in Python and TypeScript

### Security
- Constant-time HMAC comparison for token validation (use hmac.compare_digest in Python)
- Never log full webhook secrets
- Never return full webhook secrets in API responses
- Rate limiting default of 500 signals per strategy per day
- Log all webhook calls including failed attempts

### Testing
- Include example curl commands for testing each endpoint
- Test invalid token rejection
- Test rate limit rejection
- Test strategy not found rejection
- Test successful order routing

### Documentation
- Include inline code comments explaining webhook flow
- Add docstrings to new functions
- Include example JSON payloads in function docstrings

